        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-08-01T14:08:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-08-01T14:08:00-05:00" n="47"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <head>47. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>, at London<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d47fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                        974.7301/8–156. Top Secret; <gloss target="#t_Niact1">Niact</gloss>. Drafted
                        by <persName corresp="#p_RWM1">Rountree</persName> and approved and signed
                        by <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-08-01T15:08:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1956—3:08 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 6. Eyes only for the Secretary. You will
                    recall that in commenting upon possible repercussions <gloss target="#t_UK1"
                        >UK</gloss>–French military action against Egypt, <persName
                        corresp="#p_RWM1">Rountree</persName> mentioned likelihood Israeli would
                    embark upon military campaign thus associating in Arab mind Western intervention
                    with Israeli objectives. You might be interested know in conversation yesterday
                    with Russell, <persName corresp="#p_SR1">Shiloah</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d47fn2">The memorandum of this conversation by Russell,
                        dated August 1, is <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>., <gloss target="#t_NEA1"
                            >NEA</gloss> Files: Lot 59 D 518, Omega—Memos etc. July 1 to August 31,
                        1956.</note> volunteered that if Western powers take any military measures
                    in connection Suez, Israel would insist on participating in them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
